      "id": "75ea1457dc5dc1e6",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "75ea1457dc5dc1e6",
        "text": "# The roles           \n- **The Scribe** : is the one who's writing the content. He/she is collecting all the information/content about the event and he /she retrancripts by writing text. The writing style is up to him/her (crazy lyrical, frowning essay, cold meeting minutes, hot poetry). There are usually 2 scribes for each game.\n            \n- **The Iconographer** : it is the person who is in charge to illustrate the event. His/her task is to find on the Internet or to take picture of the event and to select the more appropriate to illustrate what's the scribe is writing. this role have also the job to put the right references about the picture (author...)\n            \n- **The Empathetic-Skeptic** : this person is the one who criticize or congratulate some element or content about the event. \n            \n- **The Sourcerer** : this role involves someone to double check all the information (Scribe and the empathetic-skeptic). He/she have to find articles, conversations, forum about the topic about and try to find and complete the writing by good sources, and if there is a polemic,  try to find what is about)\n            \n- **The Pollinator** : this role have 2 (or 3)task : \n                -finds conversational spaces (forums, chats, specific #hashtags,...) where the topic is actively  discussed by a bunch of people\n                - does a mapping of those conversatinal spaces (Note: *there is a useful resource at newspeak house, which is a list of all tech or political groups related to their topic democracy+technology+art*\n\n                - posts comments or tweets on the go, every hour or so, with a link to the Story that is being crafted -even though it is not complete-, making sure that it is actually relating to the interests of the people of the particular conversational space. He can then invite them to join the production by sending them one of the remaining Role cards, or simply the final result of the Story\n                -follows-up with the posts he made during the week that follows the event, to keep the conversation on and help it grow.\n\n- **The Summarian** (Animator): \n     -integrating all the contents and making them coherent with each others, especially by summarizing them \n(be it through drawings, text or audio format) and proposing a coherent esthetics to put them altogether.\n\n- **The Audio Poet**: \n    - runs 2' interviews with the participants of the event to fuel the Story with different voices and viewpoints\n    -*Sina to invent and propose playful easy to make audio formats*\n\n- **The Newage Mapper**:\n    -proposes insightful visualizations (be them digital datavisualization or handmade drawings) to give the future readers of the Story a sense of the atmosphere, spirit and mood of the event"
